Description: Double-barrel handle of Koan pottery transport amphora. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Only known from Petrie's drawing in his Journal, 1884-5, p.200, 53. Not the same as British Museum 1925, 0119.541. Name, Isidoros. There is a probability that this is to equested with British Museum 1925,0119.541.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0101)
